<!DOCTYPE refentry PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DocBook//EN">
<refentry id="tstk">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>tstk</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>tstk</refname>
    <refpurpose>a stack based programming language</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>tstk</command>
      <arg choice="opt" rep="repeat">file</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1><title>Description</title>
    <para>
      TSTK is a stack based programming language. Given no arguments
      <command>tstk</command> starts the TSTK REPL. If it is given a series of
      filenames as argument, then it runs a concatenation of the code in those
      files.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
